OL,6,FHe described Emmerson's behaviour as
OL,7,F"persistent, determined and almost
OL,8,Fdelusional," adding: "It is in some
OL,9,Fcases a mark of an offender who poses
OL,10,Fan escalating risk of sexual
OL,11,Foffending. That has proved to be the
OL,12,Fcase here. He has progressed on a very
OL,13,Fsubstantial number of occasions to
OL,14,Fserious contact offending."
OL,16,FThe court heard how victims continue
OL,17,Fto suffer lasting trauma. In
OL,18,Fstatements read to the court, women
OL,19,Fdescribed feeling increased fear,
OL,20,Fanxiety in public spaces, and a deep
OL,21,Floss of trust in the world around them.
